place of any. Harris's elucidation of this approach is a major contribution to debates on human agency, practical reason, and morality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAgent (Philosophy). 0aEthics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520922228?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922228423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520922228/original  aEBA_EMB  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles